1. Explain about Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps is a Microsoft low-code/no-code platform, that allows we can quickly build custom business applications without need any coding skills.
ğŸ‘‰ It suports creating apps with drag-and-drop components, connecting to different data sources like SharePoint, Dataverse, SQL, and more.

ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps supports building an apps mainly two types:
1. Canvas Apps.
2. Model-Driven Apps.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ”¹ Key Features of Power Apps:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1. Low-Code Development ---> Build apps easily using drag-and-drop, no deep coding needed.
2. Data Connectivity    ---> Connect your app to 500+ data sources like SharePoint, Excel, SQL, and more.
3. Responsive Design    ---> Helps a lot since our apps are accessed from mobiles and desktops.
4. Integration with Power Automate ---> For automating email approvals or status updates.
5. Prebuilt Templates and Controls ---> Use ready-made templates and components to build apps faster.
6. Offline Capability   ---> Apps can store data locally and automatically sync with the server once the connection is restored.
7. AI Builder Support   ---> Add AI features like text recognition or predictions without writing any AI code.
8. Role-Based Security  ---> To control access for different user groups such as who can create, view, edit, or delete data.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Difference between Canvas App and Model-Driven App?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ In Canvas Apps, we have full control over the appâ€™s design and layout â€” like dragging and dropping controls wherever we want.
ğŸ‘‰ I usually use Canvas Apps when I need a highly customized UI, like building forms, galleries, or designing user experiences from scratch.

ğŸ‘‰ In Model-Driven Apps, the design is based on data structure (tables, relationships) â€” so layout is automatically generated by Power Apps.
ğŸ‘‰ I prefer Model-Driven Apps for complex business processes where we already have structured data in Dataverse, like (eg, Customer Service apps). 
