5. What are Components in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Components are like reusable building blocks or custom controls that we can create once and use across multiple screens or across even apps.
ğŸ‘‰ It helps to maintain UI consistency and save development time, because we donâ€™t have to design the same thing again and again.

âœ… For Example:
1. I built a custom header component that includes the app title, navigation buttons, and user profile icon.
2. Instead of adding this manually to every screen, I just added the component.
3. So if the design or logic changes, I update the component once, and it automatically reflects across all screens â€” very efficient.

ğŸ‘‰ Components can also have input and output properties, making them dynamic and flexible based on the screen or user actions.
1ï¸âƒ£ Input Property: Passes values or information into the component (e.g., user name, color choice).
2ï¸âƒ£ Output Property: Sends data or triggers actions from inside the component (e.g., button click notification).
