6. Cascading Dropdown in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ A Cascading Dropdown filter the options in one dropdown based on the selection made in another dropdown.
âœ… For Example: when a user selects a country, only the cities related to that country appear in the second dropdown.

Dropdown 1 (Country) ---------> Items property: Distinct(CountriesCities, Country)
Dropdown 2 (City) ------------> Items property: Filter(CountriesCities, Country = Dropdown1.Selected.Result)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

7. Explain the concept of Delgations in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Delegation means pushing data operations to the data source rather than loading all data into the app and processing it locally.
ğŸ‘‰ This is important When working with large datasets â€” for example, SharePoint lists with thousands of records.
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps has a default limit of 500 records (we can increase upto max 2000 records).
ğŸ‘‰ Without delegation, Power Apps will retrieve only the first 500 records (or whatever the limit is set to), 
    which may result in incomplete or incorrect data being processed.
ğŸ‘‰ To problem slove this, we use delegable functions to handle data efficiently and correct data retrieval.
    ("Filter, Sort, and StartsWith")
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

