ğŸ‘‰ Data validation means checking the user inputs to make sure the entered data must be in the correct or complete in the expected format,
    before itâ€™s saving or processing them.
ğŸ‘‰ This helps to prevent errors as well as improves overall the data quality.

âœ… Power Apps offers built-in functions for Data Valadition:
IsBlank()  â€” checks if a field is empty.
IsMatch()  â€” validates patterns like emails or phone numbers.
IsNumeric() â€” confirms numeric inputs.
Notify()   â€” displays error messages to users.
Conditional formatting â€” like changing border colors or showing warnings based on input.
