12. Can you use Offline Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps supports offline usage by allowing us to store data locally on the user's device.
ğŸ‘‰ We mainly use Collections along with SaveData() and LoadData() functions to make the app work even without internet connectivity.
ğŸ‘‰ For example, when users are offline, we collect their inputs and save them locally using SaveData().
ğŸ‘‰ Once the network is back, we use functions like Patch() or Collect() to sync the offline data back to the server.

ğŸ”¹ For example, SaveData() saves the collection locally, and LoadData() loads it back when the app starts or reconnects.
