13. What are the limitations of Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ”¹ Power Apps have some limitations:
ğŸ‘‰ There are delegation limits when working with large data sources,
    â€” for example, only 500 to 2000 records can be retrieved unless we optimize with delegable queries.

ğŸ‘‰ Complex UI customizations or very heavy logic sometimes need workarounds because Power Apps is low-code.

ğŸ‘‰ Also, apps may perform slower if not optimized well, especially with large forms, media files, or poor network connections.

ğŸ‘‰ Licensing costs can be high if we use Premium connectors like SQL Server or Dataverse.

ğŸ‘‰ Finally, offline capabilities need to be manually handled â€” itâ€™s not automatic, so we need to build sync logic properly.
